Just days ahead of the launch, Taiwanese market research firm TrendForce has detailed alleged specs and features of the upcoming models along with their expected pricing.
In a press release, it said âApple is set to unveil four flagship devicesâthe iPhone 17, the iPhone 17 Air (tentative name), iPhone 17 Pro, and iPhone 17 Pro Maxâ.

Hereâs a look at the expected specs of 2025 iPhone lineup
iPhone 17 series leaked specs and features
Trendforce in its report says that iPhone 17 and Air are expected to feature the A19 processor, while the Pro series will adopt the A19 Pro.

In addition, the âDRAM capacity will be increased to 12 GB on the Air, Pro, and Pro Max, and NAND Flash storage will start at 256 GB for these models, scaling up to 1 TB.â
The release further states that the Air model will use a silicon anode battery and eSIM configuration to balance slimness with endurance.
It adds that the entire iPhone 17 series is expected to see major camera upgrades, with the front camera moving from 12MP to 24MP and all rear cameras raised to 48MP.

‘We have apologised to…’: Australia’s biggest bank decides not to replace human jobs with AI
The Commonwealth Bank of Australia (CBA) has backtracked on its plan to eliminate 45 customer service positions due to AI implementation, following pressure from the Finance Sector Union.
CBA admitted its assessment was flawed and offered affected employees options to remain, apply elsewhere, or exit.
